# UI components

- Use **only** shadcn/ui and React for UI. Do not introduce other UI libraries or custom design systems.
- **Add shadcn components on demand**: when a page or feature needs a component (button, card, dialog, etc.), add it with:
  ```bash
  npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>
  ```
- Components live in `components/ui/`. Use the `cn()` helper from `@/lib/utils` for class names.
- Prefer existing shadcn components over building from scratch. Add new ones as we build each page.
